annotation:
I believe that this move is unnecessary and passive now. It can be played later. Probably after c5 from black. The white should start building pawn structure on the king's field.
{Bc3 is indeed a bad move since it allows Qf4  followed by Qg4. Over the board I estimated the danger of that maneuver lower than that of the pawn breaks against the white center.}
16...Qf4  17. Ned2 Qg4 18. Rh4 Qf5 (of course 18... Q:g2 doesn't not work at all) 19. Q:f5 e:f and white get a much better pawns position.
